Not recommended if you do day trading and account is below 25K. The app and system will read day trade left differently and may flag your account as PDT if close a same day average position. Ex: Buy 100 of XYZ, and Buy 50 of XYZ, then sell 150 of XYZ same day, system will count as 2 day trades although app and webull says it is 1 day trade. If you have already done 2 day trades, your account will be flagged as PDT the next day.
replyContent: Hi there, thank you for reviewing our app! In most of cases, buy, buy, and then sell will be considered one day trade. You are flagged as a day trade only when you make over 3 day trades in any rolling 5 business day period. Please contact us at the Help Center for further assistance.

Webull is Payment for Order Flow (PFOF) which means the way they route your orders to a Market Maker who can select when they process your order and in what exchange, often at a significant disadvantage to the retail investor. Additionally, the data that Webull presents especially in the options chain is not accurate and is misleading to the retail investor, so the retail investor does not have adequate information to make informed decisions. Stay away, get established with a legitimate broker.
